sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: luxr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
In complex with HSL, LuxR binds to the Lux promoter, activating transcription from Pr BBa_R0062, and repressing transcription from Pl BBa_R0063.

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux activator, LuxR complexed to HSL. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: 2 silent point mutants were introduced in the coding sequence to remove internal XbaI and PstI sites. Mutation sites were chosen to replace codons commonly used in E. coli with codons used at a similar frequency.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lux pL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The left promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is down-regulated by the action of the Lux repressor, LuxR. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription from Pr, repressing transcription from Pl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
This promoter is based on the Vibrio fischeri quorum sensing gene promoters. Two genes LuxI and LuxR and transcribed in opposite directions as shown below. The original sequence from which the parts BBa_R0062 and BBa_R0063 were derived is shown in the picture below.Includes most of Lux reulatory region, including the LuxR binding site which activates the right promoter. A putative LuxR autorepression binding site is also identified adjacent to the -10 site of the right promoter. This 2nd site has 55% identity with the first site. Putative inverted repeats (of size 18-27 bp) also exist between these two sites (not marked above), which may represent binding sites for other regulatory proteins.

Unspecified.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I751400
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BioBrick to Tokyo Standard adapter, for XbaI, forward
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part is oligonucleotide you can buy from oligo house.
Annealed with rev oligo, this part can be incorporated into the space cut by XbaI.
This makes Biobrick part into Tokyo Standard part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
*[[BBtoTSD adapter]] 1. Cut Biobrick part with XbaI. 2. Incorporate adapter oligo. (don't forget to anneal with rev, and to make kination) 3. Now you can cut out this part by SalI or BamHI.
This makes Biobrick scar-like sequence, "tctagt" in the left and "actaga" in the right. Once oligo is ligated, you can't cut with XbaI anymore.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kenichiro Iwasaki

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I751410
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BioBrick to Tokyo Standard adapter, for SpeI, forward
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part is oligonucleotide you can buy from oligo house.
Annealed with rev oligo(BBa_I751411), this part can be incorporated into the space cut by SpeI.
This makes Biobrick part into Tokyo Standard part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
*[[BBtoTSD adapter]] 1. Cut Biobrick part with SpeI.
2. Incorporate adapter oligo. (don't forget to anneal with rev, and to make kination)
3. Now you can cut out this part by BglII or MluI.
This makes Biobrick scar-like sequence, "actaga" in the left and "tctagt" in the right. Once oligo is ligated, you can't cut with SpeI anymore.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kenichiro Iwasaki

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I751502
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: sense TWO INPUTS, activation by AHL and repression by LacI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Compared with existing BioBrick hybrid promoter R0065, this promoter is different in that its sequence is much shorter with lux box and -35 region overlapping, and that it is repressed by LacI, not cI. Also, the output is clearly detected as shown in Fig. 3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kenichiro Iwasaki

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from E. coli phage lambda (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the cI repressor based on cI repressor from bacteriophage lambda modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein. cI repressor binds to the cI regulator (BBa_R0051).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

BBa_C0051 cI repressor is based on the cI repressor from the Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LAA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
